name: The Emperor Is A Very Jealous Man
description: The reputation of the statue fragment preceded its arrival to Western Europe; after his Egyptian expedition in 1789, Napoleon Bonaparte had failed to acquire the Younger Memnon for France. Although the British Museum expected delivery of the antiquity in 1818, the Younger Memnon did not arrive in London until 1821. Shelley published his poems before the statue fragment of Ozymandias arrived in Britain.
